aa(lp148
VWhat about résumés? We did a study in which we had
p149
aVpeople apply for a job, and they could apply for a job
p150
aVeither with a traditional paper résumé, or on LinkedIn,
p151
aVwhich is a social networking site like Facebook,
p152
aVbut for professionals \u2014 involves the same information as a résumé.
p153
aVAnd what we found, to many people's surprise,
p154
aVwas that those LinkedIn résumés were more honest
p155
aVon the things that mattered to employers, like your
p156
aVresponsibilities or your skills at your previous job.
p157
aa(lp158
VHow about Facebook itself?
p159
aVYou know, we always think that hey, there are these
p160
aVidealized versions, people are just showing the best things
p161
aVthat happened in their lives. I've thought that many times.
p162
aVMy friends, no way they can be that cool and have good of a life.
p163
aVWell, one study tested this by examining people's personalities.
p164
aVThey had four good friends of a person judge their personality.
p165
aVThen they had strangers, many strangers,
p166
aVjudge the person's personality just from Facebook,
p167
